I do:<p><pre><code>    .thing {
      position: relative;
    }
    .thing .child {
      width: 50px;
      height: 50px;
      position: absolute;
      top: 50%;
      margin-top: -25px; /* half of height */
    }
</code></pre>
Or else if it&#x27;s text I just make the line-height the same height as the parent element. That keeps things vertically centred :)
